5:
We're supposed to investigate an
adventurer?
10:
I don't know... It sounds a bit
underhanded to me. We don't
usually engage in background
checks.
15:
Hold your horses! We're not asking
you to dig the skeletons out of her
closet.
16:
It's just, it can be hard when you're
getting your footholds in the
adventuring world. The old guard
already have each other.
19:
So we need to ensure that the
newbies will get along swimmingly!
Hence taking a peek at their
personalities and behaviors!
24:
Hm. Group chemistry IS crucial to
the health of any squad.
29:
Exactly! Feel free to take this mission
at your own pace, using whatever
methods you see fit.
37:
That's her, Meryll. She seems mature
and levelheaded. Should make for
an ideal candidate.
41:
Really? Then why did they ask us to
look into her? Maybe we should just
talk to her...
47: What is that she's doing? Drawing?
48:
This doesn't bode well; it's not
typical behavior for an adventurer.
51:
Uh, don't we all have our own
hobbies?
71:
You're right! It looks like she's
passing out books!
74:
No, those were much too thin to be
books. They looked more like
ledgers... Adventurer records?
Account books?
78:
Follow her, Alk! We have to find out
what she's doing!
83:
You outdid yourself, Meryll! I can't
believe you put THAT in the story. We
were all spellbound.
86:
Hehe. I'm just thankful someone
appreciates true art.
87:
Now, let's see if my latest work still
whets your appetite!
90:
Ah! Only you would think of such an
excellent ship! Here, let me pay you
for the trouble.
102:
Alk! Grab the notebook! That's our
evidence!
111:
Uh, it looks like a sketchbook... No, it's
a comic.
115:
And this is diary. Or, wait, a novella?
"The touch of your slender fingers
takes my breath away..."
129:
What is the meaning of this, you
buffoons! What right do you have to
interrupt our meeting!
133:
We are Light and Alk, and we've
come on behalf of the guild to
investigate you! These books are
proof of your shady actions!
137:
The guild? Why are they
investigating me?! *GASP* D-do
they want to kill me?!
142:
Why would they kill you?! *GASP*
Unless you're hiding some nefarious
plot inside these tomes!
146:
Ahem, Light. I think you've misread
the situation.
150:
How dare you! I'll have you know I'm
an avid reader!
158:
Just listen, Alk! "With one bite, his
body, normally taut and firm,
became unraveled. Submissive."
171:
Forgive me, Meryll. I didn't realize
that was a meeting for aspiring
romance novelists.
172:
As promised, we won't say a peep to
the guild. So all's well that ends well?
177: A promise is not nearly enough!
182:
I don't understand why this is such a
secret? Art is a noble undertaking.
185:
W-will you please stop! We're not
trying to make classic literature!
188:
But the only way I'll feel s-safe, is if I
keep a close watch on you two!
192:
Well, we were observing you in
secret first, so I suppose fair is fair.
197:
Hm. You want to learn our secrets,
don't you? Have something to
blackmail us with? Not bad.
203:
Heh... Hehehehe! I never thought I
would gain entrée with a group of
experienced adventurers so soon!
204:
I can't let this chance escape me! I'll
need to learn enough about them to
repay the embarrassment they've
caused!
208: This is going to be good!
213:
*gulp* Why do I feel something
sinister in the air? Do you think we
should've let her join us?
217:
Hah. Maybe something SINister is in
the air?
